			<td><br><img src=/shared_files/techspeakers_photos/Baker_Stephen.jpg align=left valign="top">&nbsp;Stephen Baker is NPD’s primary hardware analyst.  He offers expert insight and commentary to clients and the media about PC sales and trends, PC-related technologies, the business and selling of consumer technology, as well other topics. <br><br>
Baker joined NPD when it acquired PC Data Inc., in March 2001.  At PC Data, he was the principal hardware analyst and director of the overall hardware POS business.  Prior to joining PC Data, he was a senior analyst in the distribution channels service at International Data Corporation (IDC).  He began his career at Staples in 1986, helping to open the first office superstore. 
